{"c":"q/ \"Anarchy is a radical disturbance of the state, a disruption of the state's attempt to set itself up or erect itself into a whole (s'eriger en Tout). In our terms, anarchy is the creation of interstitial space within the state, the continual questioning from below of any attempt to establish order from above. We might say that ethical anarchy is the experience of the multiple singularities of the encounter with others that defines the experience of sociality. Each of these singularities overwhelms and undoes us and we can never do enough in response.\" // Simon Critchley, Infinitely Demanding, 2012, 122","p":{"x":604,"y":46},"t":0,"u":"anarchic14","r":[],"d":[2020,6,15,15,48,53],"db":"anarchic","_id":"AQIIXzM7lMIc5SR9"}
